Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) into half moons. Chop the @new potatoes{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks) and pop them on a #baking tray{} with the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}. Drizzle over a splash of @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30%minutes}. After ~{10%minutes}, turn the potatoes and add the onion. Return to the oven to finish cooking.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lemon{1/2}(zested and cut in half). Rinse the @baby spinach{1}(rinsed in a colander) in a #colander{} under cold water. Keep to one side. Don't forget to add the onion to your potatoes, do any washing up that needs doing and then move on to the next step.

Season the @cod fillets{2} with a pinch of @salt{}, a splash of @oil{} and a sprinkling of lemon zest. Rub the oil and salt into the cod. Keep to one side.

When the potatoes have ~{10-12%minutes} cooking time left, heat a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, carefully lay in the fish (no oil!) skin-side down and cook until the skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. When the skin is crispy, carefully turn and cook the flesh side, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: The fish is cooked when the centre is opaque.

Remove from the pan and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe the #frying pan{} out with #kitchen towel{}.

Return the empty frying pan to medium heat and add a splash of @oil{}. Add the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated), cook for ~{30%seconds} and add the spinach. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently until the spinach has wilted, ~{3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, squeeze the lemon juice over the cod. Serve the cod on a bed of garlicky spinach with the pancetta roasties alongside. Enjoy!